titles.title: To designate the Federal building located at 300 4th Street, Northeast, in the District of Columbia, as the "Daniel Webster Senate Page Residence", and for other purposes.

vote.text: Introduced in the Senate, read twice, considered, read the third time, and passed without amendment by Voice Vote.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.
Referred to the House Committee on Public Works + Transportation.

committee.name: House Committee on Public Works + Transportation

action.text: Referred to the Subcommittee on Public Buildings and Grounds.

bill.summary: 11/20/1993--Introduced. Designates the Federal building located at 300 4th Street, Northeast, Washington, D.C., as the Daniel Webster Senate Page Residence.
